meanings.definition: A printed copy of a document or image.
meanings.sent1: I needed a printout of the recipe to follow along.
meanings.sent2: She handed me a printout of the presentation slides.
meanings.sent3: The cat knocked over the stack of printouts, creating a paper blizzard.
meanings.sent4: His smile was like a bright printout in the dull room.
meanings.sent5: The printout of the map helped us navigate through the forest easily.

meanings.definition: The act of producing a printed copy.
meanings.sent1: The printout of the report was ready for the meeting.
meanings.sent2: The printout of the document was clear and easy to read.
meanings.sent3: The printer made a strange noise during the printout process.
meanings.sent4: Her laughter echoed in the room like a joyful printout.
meanings.sent5: The printout of the contract was signed and filed for safekeeping.
